# Ignore smoke-fixture files generated by non-canonical runs (e.g. from tmp/
# scratch directories or ad-hoc invocations).  The ONE committed fixture
# (smoke-fixture-f0640942ad73.json) is explicitly tracked via a !-exception
# below so it stays in the repo as the S1 determinism proof.
#
# Why this pattern exists: run.mjs uses a content-hash of the artifact body
# (with measured_at excluded) to name the smoke-fixture file, so reruns on the
# same corpus+inputs always overwrite the same file.  If the hash algorithm or
# inputs ever change legitimately, delete the old committed fixture and commit
# the new one in its place — the !-exception below must be updated in that
# commit.  Do not leave both the old and new fixture in the repo.
#
# Finding B10-S1-SMOKE-FIXTURE-NONDETERMINISM-001 — Slice 1 reviewer.

smoke-fixture-*.json
!smoke-fixture-f0640942ad73.json
